Founded in 1998, the "Royal Spas of Europe". Members are traditional spas which have a rich history and tradition of royal patronage - counting kings, queens and emperors, dukes and all branches of the aristocracy among their guests and offering an infrastructure with an exceptional quality of expertise and excellence.&#xd;
&#xd;
The ESPA was coordinator of an EU funded project "RomanSpas of Europe" which has brought European thermal spas and health resorts which are from Roman origin.&#xd;
&#xd;
ESPA supports the Tourism for Growth and Jobs Manifesto initiative of the European tourism stakeholders.&#xd;
&#xd;
The ESPA is in close cooperation with the International Society of Medical Hydrology and Climatology (ISMH).&#xd;
&#xd;
The ESPA is official member of the CALPYSO action group of the tourism unit of the EU. As well as member of their senior expert group.&#xd;
&#xd;
The two certificates EUROPESPA med and EUROPESPA wellness signify international standards of quality as defined by ESPA.&#xd;
&#xd;
Members benefits: &#xd;
&#xd;
■Commercial success thanks to high levels of quality certified by a well known association. &#xd;
&#xd;
■PR and communication via the international web portal: www.europespa.eu . &#xd;
&#xd;
■Outstanding reputation in their own sector and among their main clients.   &#xd;
&#xd;
■Continuous improvement to international top quality within just a few years. &#xd;
&#xd;
■Anonymous quality checks to keep them aware of their own position against international competition. &#xd;
&#xd;
Criteria and auditing&#xd;
The some 400 audit questions for EUROPESPA med are based on 4 main sets of national and international rules on safety, hygiene and therapy infrastructure.&#xd;
For EUROPESPA wellness (safety, hygiene, wellness infrastructure and service quality), about 350 questions are examined on your premises while another 600 items regarding service quality are tested anonymously.&#xd;
At least 80% of all the criteria as well as certain basic requirements have to be met. These results are then compared to subsequent audits to ensure that continuous mprovement takes place.
